# {{serviceName}}

An OAuth 2.0 authorization server scaffolded by [Foundry](https://github.com/alphonso77/foundry).

- **Token strategy:** `{{tokenStrategy}}`
- **PKCE:** {{#ifEquals pkce true}}enabled{{else}}disabled{{/ifEquals}}
- **Datastore:** {{datastore}}
- **Deploy target:** AWS ECS (Fargate)

## Getting started

```bash
npm install
cp .env.example .env   # then fill in secrets
npm run db:init        # drop (if exists), create, and migrate the Postgres schema
npm run dev            # start the server on PORT (default 3000)
```

To access the swagger UI, navigate to: `http://localhost:3000/docs`

Build & typecheck:

```bash
npm run build
npm run typecheck
```

## Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/health` | Liveness probe. |
| GET | `/oauth/authorize` | Issues an authorization code (`?client_id=&scope=`{{#ifEquals pkce true}}`&code_challenge=`{{/ifEquals}}). |
| POST | `/oauth/token` | Exchanges an authorization code or refresh token for tokens. |
{{#ifEquals tokenStrategy "local-jwt"}}| GET | `/oauth/userinfo` | Protected — returns the authenticated principal (`sub`/`client_id`/`scope`) for a valid access token. |
{{/ifEquals}}{{#ifEquals apiDocs true}}| GET | `/docs` | Interactive Swagger UI for the OAuth endpoints. |
{{/ifEquals}}

{{#ifEquals apiDocs true}}
## Interactive API docs

With the server running, open **http://localhost:3000/docs** for a Swagger UI of the
OAuth endpoints.
{{#ifEquals pkce true}}
The Authorization Code flow is wired with **PKCE**: click **Authorize**, and Swagger UI
generates a `code_verifier`/`code_challenge` (S256) in the browser and runs a real
authorization-code-with-PKCE exchange against `/oauth/authorize` → `/oauth/token`.
{{else}}
The Authorization Code flow is wired into the **Authorize** button so you can run a real
`/oauth/authorize` → `/oauth/token` exchange from the browser.
{{/ifEquals}}
{{#ifEquals tokenStrategy "local-jwt"}}
**Two-click token demo:** click **Authorize** (runs the full {{#ifEquals pkce true}}PKCE {{/ifEquals}}flow and holds
an access token), then expand **GET `/oauth/userinfo`** and click **Execute**. Swagger attaches the
bearer token automatically and the endpoint returns the authenticated principal — exercising the whole
token flow in two clicks. The raw **POST `/oauth/token`** form is intentionally omitted from the docs:
its one-time authorization code is consumed by the Authorize button, so a manual "Try it out" never has
a fresh code.
{{/ifEquals}}
{{/ifEquals}}

{{#ifEquals tokenStrategy "local-jwt"}}
Tokens are minted locally as JWTs signed with `JWT_SECRET`.
{{else}}
Tokens are obtained from the external IdP at `IDP_ISSUER`. Wire the exchange in `src/auth/tokens.ts`.
{{/ifEquals}}

## Registering additional clients

`schema.sql` seeds one default client. To register **another** client (e.g. a front-end app or
another service) without editing SQL, set these before `npm run db:init` — the migration registers
it idempotently on top of the default:

| Env var | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `SEED_CLIENT_ID` | Client identifier. When unset, no extra client is registered (default behavior). |
| `SEED_CLIENT_REDIRECT_URIS` | Comma-separated list of allowed redirect URIs. |
| `SEED_CLIENT_SECRET` | Optional. Leave unset for a public client (PKCE). |

```bash
SEED_CLIENT_ID=foundry-portal \
SEED_CLIENT_REDIRECT_URIS=http://localhost:5173/callback \
  npm run db:init
```

